        "clinicalNotes": "The patient presented with a chief complaint of sudden weakness, localized to the left side of the body. The onset time was 2026-05-16T21:32. The duration of symptoms was 0.00 hours. Factors affecting the symptoms included high blood pressure. Associated symptoms included none.\n\nMedical history included diabetes mellitus. The patient reported gutka use. The last documented feed time was 2026-05-16T21:32.\n\nOn physical examination, general assessment was parallel. Heart sounds S1 and S2 were present. The abdomen was soft and tender, with present bowel sounds. Lungs showed normal air entry, with both left and right lungs clear. Cardiovascular system assessment noted no anxiety, normal jugular venous pressure (JVP), and ++ edema grade. Pulse rate volume was weak, character was smooth upstroke, and rhythm was regular.\n\nNeurological examination revealed normal vision. Weakness was not present. Facial asymmetry was present. Aphasia was present. Dysarthria was present. Gazeparesis was present. Cerebellar signs were present. Ataxia was present. The swallow test was positive. Right pupil size was 2, and left pupil size was 1. Right upper limb (UL) motor power was 2, and left UL motor power was 2. Right lower limb (LL) motor power was 3, and left LL motor power was 3. Right UL sensory was normal. Right LL sensory was absent. Left UL sensory was reduced. Left LL sensory was absent. Right plantar reflex was mute, and left plantar reflex was mute.\n\nCT scan findings indicated ischemic stroke. Clot/bleed location was adsf.\n\nThe provisional diagnosis was df.\n\nThe patient was seen by a registrar at 2026-05-16T21:33. The initial assessment was completed at 2026-05-16T21:33.",
